Summary:
This netlist is the simulator-ready form of the RC low-pass schematic. It is the same first-order filter described in the `.asc` file, but expressed as a flat SPICE deck.
The output node is the top of the capacitor, so the deck naturally implements a low-pass transfer from source to that node.

Line-by-line:
`Vin N001 0 SINE(1 1 25000) AC 1` defines the excitation.
`R1 OUT N001 1` places the resistor between input and output.
`C1 OUT 0 100µ` connects the capacitor from output to ground.
`.ac dec 1000 10 100k` sweeps the AC response.
The remaining comment lines document the design intent and cutoff formula.
`.backanno` and `.end` finish the deck.
